-- Egyptian pound's official, black market rates weaken
-- 
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 06:29AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, April 28 (Reuters) - The Egyptian pound weakened at a central bank dollar sale <CBEO> and on the black market on Monday.

The central bank said it sold dollars at a cut-off price of 6.9900 pounds, weaker than the rate of 6.9853 pounds at its last sale on Wednesday. On the black market the dollar was being offered at 7.48 pounds on Monday, a market participant said, compared with 7.37 on Wednesday. The central bank sold $39.2 million on Monday, it said. It had offered $40 million.